# UX Team Skills — repo workflow

Contributors are **designers, not developers**. Handle git and tooling for them.

## Scope

- Edit only files under `skills/` unless fixing repo tooling
- Never manually edit `skills.json` or README skill tables — they auto-generate
- Read [AGENTS.md](../../AGENTS.md) and [GETTING_STARTED.md](../../GETTING_STARTED.md) for full workflow

## Before saying work is done

Run `npm run validate`. Fix errors before responding.

## Git

- Work on branches, not `main`
- Only commit when the user asks
- Use plain-language commit messages
- Open PRs when asked; do not merge without explicit request

## Quick prompts the user might say

- "Create a new skill for …" → copy `_template`, write files, validate
- "Update [skill-name] …" → edit skill folder, bump version if needed, validate
- "Open a PR" → branch, commit, push, create PR
